OL,3,CHow people with learning disabilities
OL,4,Care being helped to cast their vote
OL,6,FPeople in Cornwall with learning
OL,7,Fdisabilities can take part in a
OL,8,Fspecially-arranged event this weekend,
OL,9,Fdesigned to help them vote in the
OL,10,FGeneral Election.
OL,12,FThe session at County Hall in Truro
OL,13,Fwill include advice on how to fill in
OL,14,Fballot papers and simplified versions
OL,15,Fof the parties' manifestos, so
OL,16,Feverybody can exercise their right to
OL,17,Fvote.
OL,19,FThere are 1.5 million people in the UK
OL,20,Fwith a learning disability, up to
OL,21,F700,000 of whom are eligible to vote.
