OL,3,CHow people with learning disabilities
OL,4,Care being helped to cast their vote
OL,6,FAngie Emrys-Jones, from the Cornwall
OL,7,FDown's Syndrome Support Group, said:
OL,8,F"There are reasonable adjustments that
OL,9,Fcan be made around voting.
OL,11,F"You can take take somebody with you
OL,12,Fif you're a bit anxious on the day, if
OL,13,Fyou're a bit concerned whether it's
OL,14,Fcomplicated.
OL,16,F"You can have somebody go in the
OL,17,Fballot box and read the candidates out
OL,18,Fto you. You can have enlarged print
OL,19,Fand have somebody help you make a mark
OL,20,Fon the paper.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/5
