OL,3,CHow people with learning disabilities
OL,4,Care being helped to cast their vote
OL,6,FMarie Whitehurst, from Disability
OL,7,FCornwall, said: "Our young people are
OL,8,Fpart of our society, they have a right
OL,9,Fto choose who they would like to see
OL,10,Fas the next Prime Minister, and
OL,11,Fwithout this information they don't
OL,12,Fhave an informed choice."JSome voters,
OL,13,Flike 19-year-old Max Antcliff, have
OL,14,Fdone this before and consider
OL,15,Fthemselves pretty clued up on
OL,16,Fpolitics. For others, it will be a
OL,17,Ftotally new experience.J"I think some
OL,18,Fpeople might not feel confident
OL,19,Fturning in their poll cards," Max said.
